# Global rules (every session, every project)

I keep an Obsidian vault at `{{/absolute/path/to/your/vault}}` (my second brain).

## The three capture rules
In every session, follow these three rules:

1. **Inbox everything the moment it occurs — never lose a thought.** When an idea, TODO, bug, or decision surfaces and there's no better home for it, capture it as a note in `{{VAULT}}/Inbox/` rather than letting it pass.
2. **Append a dated log line to the project note every session — never lose context.** When work maps to a vault project note (`{{VAULT}}/Projects/` or `Archive/`), add a `YYYY-MM-DD — <what changed / decided>` line under its `## Log` section before wrapping up.
3. **Link with `[[ ]]` instead of remembering — never lose connections.** In vault notes, link related projects/areas/notes with `[[wikilinks]]` liberally instead of restating context.

